Exercise 1. Continent-wide life expectancy

1. Compute the mean life expectancy and GDP per capita for each (continent, year)

#Compute the mean life expectancy and GDP per capita for each (continent, year)
table<-gapminder %>%
  group_by(continent, year) %>%
  summarize(
    mean_lifeExp = mean(lifeExp),
    mean_gdpPercap = mean(gdpPercap),
    .groups = "drop"
  )
table

2.Do an animated scatterplot of continent life expectancy vs.GDP (transition_time(year))

# Animated scatterplot of continent life expectancy vs. GDP
plot1 <- ggplot(table, aes(x = mean_gdpPercap, y = mean_lifeExp, color = continent)) +
  geom_point(size = 4) +
  labs(title = 'Ao: {frame_time}', 
       x = 'PIB per cpita promedio', 
       y = 'Esperanza de vida promedio') +
  transition_time(year) +
  ease_aes('linear')

#Force rendering
animate(plot1, renderer = gifski_renderer())

Exercise 2. Inequality of GDP/capita across countries over time

1.For each year, compute the inter-quartile range of the GDP/capita across countries.

# Create a new (grouped) tibble by year
by_year = group_by(gapminder, year)
# Compute the inter-quartile range of GDP per capita for each year
iqr_gdpPercap = summarize(by_year,iqr = IQR(gdpPercap))
iqr_gdpPercap

2.Do a scatterplot of IQR vs.year. Add lines to the plot

# Scatterplot of IQR vs. year with lines
ggplot(iqr_gdpPercap, aes(x = year, y =iqr)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_line() +
  labs(title = 'Inter-quartile range of GDP per capita over time', 
       x = 'Year', 
       y = 'IQR of GDP per capita')
